{
  "module": "02-state-management.md",
  "group": "02 — State Management",
  "apiCount": 10,
  "apis": [
    {
      "name": "@State",
      "purpose": "Built-in decorator marking a component's local state variable as reactive; UI re-renders on change",
      "anchor": "state",
      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "@Prop",
      "purpose": "Built-in decorator for one-way data binding from parent to child component",
      "anchor": "prop",
      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "@Link",
      "purpose": "Built-in decorator for two-way data binding between parent and child components",
      "anchor": "link",
      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "@ObjectLink",
      "purpose": "Built-in decorator for sharing an @Observed class object reference between parent and child",
      "anchor": "objectlink",
      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "@Provide",
      "purpose": "Built-in decorator providing data from an ancestor component for @Consume descendants, with optional allowOverride",
      "anchor": "provide",
      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "@Consume",
      "purpose": "Built-in decorator receiving data provided by ancestor @Provide, establishing two-way sync",
      "anchor": "consume",
      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "@Watch",
      "purpose": "Decorator (Watch) that registers a callback on state variable changes, callback name passed as string argument",
      "anchor": "watch",
      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "AppStorage",
      "purpose": "Global application-level UI state storage with key-value pair management, available from API version 7",
      "anchor": "appstorage",
      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "LocalStorage",
      "purpose": "Page-level UI state storage, each UIAbility can create independent instances, available from API version 9",
      "anchor": "localstorage",
      "status": "found"
    },
    {
      "name": "PersistentStorage",
      "purpose": "Persistent UI state storage persisting AppStorage data to files on disk, available from API version 7",
      "anchor": "persistentstorage",
      "status": "found"
    }
  ],
  "notableFindings": [
    "@State / @Prop / @Link / @ObjectLink / @Provide / @Consume are built-in decorators (language-level features) with no import path or standalone API Reference files; only ProvideOptions is documented in the API Reference",
    "AppStorage, LocalStorage, and PersistentStorage are global objects, no import required — but API version 10+ deprecates old PascalCase methods (Link/Prop/etc.) in favor of camelCase (link/prop/etc.)",
    "@ohos.arkui.StateManagement (API 12+) provides V2 equivalents: AppStorageV2 and PersistenceV2, imported via '@kit.ArkUI'",
    "V2 persistent storage with PersistenceV2 requires @Type decorator for nested class properties and @ObservedV2/@Trace for reactivity"
  ],
  "missingApis": []
}

